This project restarts some applications that bugs on linux resume, like dropbox and empathy.  It works with pm-utils resume event. Applications to be restarted can be configurated with a json file.


How To Configure:

Example: 
{
    "dropbox" : {
        "cmdline" : "/home/fenrrir/.dropbox-dist/dropbox"
    },
    "empathy" : {
        "cmdline" : "empathy",
        "subprocesses" : [
            "/usr/lib/empathy/empathy-auth-client",
            "/usr/lib/telepathy/mission-control-5",
            "/usr/lib/telepathy/telepathy-logger",
            "/usr/bin/python /usr/lib/telepathy/telepathy-butterfly",
            "/usr/lib/telepathy/telepathy-gabble",
            "/usr/lib/telepathy/telepathy-salut"
        ]
    }
}

The configuration file is a json object that specifies application's name and it's command line. Also, it is possible to specify application's subprocesses to be stopped before restarting. Put the configuration file under ".perfectresume.conf" in your home directory.  

How to Install:

Copy example.conf to $HOME/.perfectresume.conf
Copy notifier.py at /usr/lib/pm-utils/sleep.d/
Add service.py to your gnome-session


Dependencies:

Python 2.6
pm-utils
python-psutil 0.2.1
